net.proteusframework.ui.search

Class SearchUIImpl.Options

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.proteusframework.ui.search.SearchUIImpl.Options
  • Enclosing class:
    SearchUIImpl

    public static final class SearchUIImpl.Options
extends java.lang.Object
    Options for the SearchUI.

    If no limits are specified, the SearchUI will use a QLRowDataModel.

    Author:
    Russ Tennant (russ@proteus.co)

      • setSearchSuppliers

        public SearchUIImpl.Options setSearchSuppliers(java.util.List<SearchSupplier> searchSuppliers)
        Set the search suppliers.

        Required.

        If no limits are specified on the SearchModel, the SearchUI will use a QLRowDataModel.

        If multiple SearchSuppliers are configured, then the SearchUI will allow switching between them. Another option is to create multiple SearchUIImpls. See SearchUIApp.addSearchUI(TabItemDisplay, SearchUI) for that method.
        Parameters:
        searchSuppliers - the search suppliers.
        Returns:
        this.

      • setSearchSuppliersLabel

        Returns:
        this.

      • setShowDefaultSelectionWidgets

        public SearchUIImpl.Options setShowDefaultSelectionWidgets(boolean showDefaultSelectionWidgets)

        Parameters:
